The Lagos State government has received basic essential medical supplies donated by Nosak Group to support the state government in the fight against the novel COVID-19 pandemic.
 
While presenting the donation at the office of the Permanent Secretary, Lagos State Primary Health Care Board, the company’s Corporate Communications Manager, Kenneth Adejumoh, commended the state government for the swiftness in managing the pandemic and showing the ability to curtail its spread.
 
“As an organisation, it is in our culture to identify with the Government and the people of the state in times like this with the donation of basic medical supplies in support of the efforts put in place to manage the medical crisis from COVID-19, which has affected our usual activities,” he said.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .